_comment=jawiki redirects to ウカノミタマ|1=Ukanomitama|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q3080728}}.<ref name="Asao Tourism"/> ** In 1909 (Meiji 42), five local shrines in {{ill|Okagami Village|ja|岡上村|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Okagami Village|1=Okagami|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11471931}} were merged under the name "Okagami Shrine." The site of the former {{ill|Suwa Shrine|ja|諏訪神社|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa Shrine|qq=}} in the center of the village was chosen for the new shrine to promote unity among villagers.<ref name="Asao Tourism">[https://asao-kankou.jp/?page_id=1992 Okagami Shrine (おかがみじんじゃ)] Asao Tourism, Kawasaki/Asao Tourism Association, accessed January 6, 2022.</ref> See also {{ill|Okagami#Facilities|ja|岡上#施設|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Okagami#Facilities|1=Okagami|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11471928}} and {{ill|History of Okagami Village|ja|岡上村#歴史|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/History of Okagami Village|1=Okagami|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11471931}}. * Okagami Shrine (おかがみじんじゃ) - The former name of {{ill|Okanomiya Shrine (Fukaya City)|ja|岡廼宮神社 (深谷市)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Okanomiya Shrine (Fukaya City)|1=Okanomiya Shrine|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q119929455}}, located in {{ill|Fukaya, Saitama|en|Fukaya, Saitama|WD=Q734532|lt=Fukaya City|1=Fukaya, Saitama}}, {{ill|Saitama Prefecture|en|Saitama Prefecture|WD=Q128186|lt=Saitama Prefecture|1=Saitama Prefecture}}.
